 level this has less to do with a world view inspired by spirituality and philosophical traditions and more to do with observable evidence about the universe viriditas talk   november  utc viriditas that may be true but in this context macks belief in connection is based on the eastern influences present in the field of transpersonal psychology since dr mack was a psychiatrist not a biologist or a chemist perhaps an interlink to transpersonal psychology could be worked into the paragraph   december  utc — preceding unsigned comment added by  talk investigationedit according to daniel sheehan macks attorney the committees draft report… this addition is problematic and i am not sure how best to resolve it although the sentence begins with the conditional statement according to the next hundred words of sheehans excessivelylong quote give the impression of being direct quotes from the ad hoc committees draft report but they are simply sheehans interpretation of that report or his interpretation of the beliefs of the authors of that report relying upon only one persons perspective for such a large section it is a full third of the investigation section does not conform to best practices so i will trim back sheehans remarks a bit and i will advise finding a second and third source to convey more info about the report a secondary minor problem associated with this addition is that sheehan is introduced as macks attorney before the next paragraph which more properly introduced eric macleish and daniel sheehan as macks attorneys willbueche talk   april  utc update i made sheehans quote more succinct but it is still problematic because it is partly false sheehan said they demanded mack use every possible available battery of standard psychological tests which might conceivably explain the report as the product of some known form of clinical psychosis but in fact the report emphasized that absent any evidence of mental illness mack should have considered nonpathological psychological explanations sheehans claim they expected mack would find clinical psychosis is hyperbole i checked the report myself to see what they wrote again this is the problem with using one person as a sourcewillbueche talk   april  utc external links modifiededit hello fellow wikipedians i have just modified one external link on john e mack please take a moment to review my edit if you have any questions or need the bot to ignore the links or the page altogether please visit this simple faq for additional information i made the following changes added archive httpswebarchiveorgwebhttpwwwufopsicomarticlesjohnmackhtml to httpwwwufopsicomarticlesjohnmackhtml when you have finished reviewing my changes you may follow the instructions on the template below to fix any issues with the urls you may set the checked on this template to true or failed to let other editors know you reviewed the change if you find any errors please use the tools below to fix them or call an editor by setting needhelp to your help request if you have discovered urls which were erroneously considered dead by the bot you can report them with this tool if you found an error with any archives or the urls themselves you can fix them with this tool if you are unable to use these tools you may set needhelpyour help request on this template to request help from an experienced user please include details about your problem to help other editors cheers—internetarchivebot report bug   april  utc retrieved from httpsenwikipediaorgwindexphptitletalkjohnemackoldid categories bclass biography articlesbclass biography science and academia articlesunknownimportance biography science and academia articlesscience and academia work group articleswikipedia requested photographs of scientists and academicswikiproject biography articlesbclass paranormal articlesunknownimportance paranormal articleswikiproject paranormal articlesbclass parapsychology articlesunknownimportance parapsychology articles navigation menu pe